{
  "texts": [
    "It's as if the machine can replicate and even someday replace human intelligence.",
    "It also implies that the brain works in broadly similar ways to a computer, as if the brain were just a calculating machine working in binary notation.",
    "But machines and humans are profoundly different.",
    "Computers are much better than humans at some things.",
    "In their tedious and laborious calculating ways, they can relieve humans of boring mental tasks."
  ]
}